tre will result in better outcomes for the most vulnerable? Moreover, it also considers those young people who traditionally bypass child protection services but remain at risk of harm. These are critical questions for both policy and practice in understanding the reforms Munro states are required. Contributions from leading experts working in the child protection system review current safeguarding policy and explore the future after Munro.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Jan 2023) 0aChild welfarexGovernment policyzGreat Britain. 0aChild welfarezGreat Britain. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Social Work.2bisacsh1 aAtkinson, Maggie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBlyth, Maggie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aClifton, Jenny, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCoombe, Andrew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFox, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGreen, Colin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHolt, Amanda, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPreston-Shoot, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRees, Gwyther, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSolomon, Enver, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aSolomon, Enver, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStein, Mike, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2013-1995z978311119621340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781447304913423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781447304913/original